Snap 7 March 2020 Updated 32 seconds ago 
China posts first trade deficit in two years 
 
China's exports fell in February, as expected. But imports were not as negative as predicted, as imports of medical-related supplies surged. That resulted in a trade deficit for China, the first since March 2018 
Shutterstock 
120719-image-cargo-trade-export-import-china.jpg 
Share 
Author 
Iris Pang 
